DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGchoicemacros.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

@freq = (
    random(1,10,1),
    random(1,10,1),
    random(1,10,1),
    random(10,15,1),
    random(10,15,1),
    random(15,20,1),
    random(1,10,1));
$total = 0; 
$total += $_ for @freq; 

@rel_freq = map { $_/$total } @freq; 

BEGIN_PGML

One study was performed in an attempt to determine the day of the week when road rage occurs most often.  Complete the table below.

[#
    [.Day of the Week.] [.Frequency.] [.Relative Frequency .]*{headerrow => 1}
    [. Sunday .] [. [$freq[0]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[0]} .]*
    [. Monday .] [. [$freq[1]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[1]} .]*
    [. Tuesday .] [. [$freq[2]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[2]} .]*
    [. Wednesday .] [. [_]{$freq[3]} .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[3]} .]*
    [. Thursday .] [. [$freq[4]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[4]} .]*
    [. Friday .] [. [$freq[5]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[5]} .]*
    [. Saturday .] [. [$freq[6]] .] [. [_]{$rel_freq[6]} .]*
    [. **Total** .] [. [$total] .] [. 1.]*
#]{padding=>[0.25, 0.25]}

END_PGML

$subtotal = $total - $freq[3]; 

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
First, the total number of observations from the table is [$total].  The sum of the frequencies need to be this value.  The frequencies other than Wednesday is [$subtotal], therefore the Wednesday observation is [` [$total] - [$subtotal] = [$freq[3]] `].

The relative frequency is found by dividing the frequency by the total.  The result is:


[#
    [.Day of the Week.] [.Frequency.] [.Relative Frequency .]*{headerrow => 1}
    [. Sunday .] [. [$freq[0]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[0]) @] .]*
    [. Monday .] [. [$freq[1]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[1]) @] .]*
    [. Tuesday .] [. [$freq[2]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[2]) @] .]*
    [. Wednesday .] [. [$freq[3]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[3]) @] .]*
    [. Thursday .] [. [$freq[4]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[4]) @] .]*
    [. Friday .] [. [$freq[5]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[5]) @] .]*
    [. Saturday .] [. [$freq[6]] .] [. [@sprintf("%.4f", $rel_freq[6]) @] .]*
    [. **Total** .] [. [$total] .] [. 1.]*
#]{padding=>[0.25, 0.25]}
END_PGML_SOLUTION
